{
  "stem": "12462.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I traveled with him a good deal when he made inspections and investigations, and I helped him write his reports, which were made to a General [?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Lee. ?] I forget [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Lee's ?] first name, but a General [?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Lee. ?]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In North Africa, mainly in Algeria, but a time or two to-- to Morocco and once to Gibraltar.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Until sometime in about maybe May of 1944.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But by that time, I had been-- a friend of mine who was in the Office of Strategic Services, OSS, fellow by the name of Gerhard Van Arkel, recruited me to come with OSS.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And my main task there was training anti-Nazi Germans who had been recruited through the British Pioneer Corps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They'd-- most of them had fought in France, and then the British had covered them and put them in the-- the British Pioneer Corps.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they were very glad to-- to-- those that we recruited-- to serve as potential agents.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I think out of 18 that we trained, 17 of them jumped in, parachuted in, ahead of the American troops when the American troops were already invading German territory.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I was in Oran, Algeria, when I was recruited to go into OSS in Algiers, and then I stayed in Algiers during this training operation.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had some houses, which were secret houses, both on the outskirts of Algiers and some ways out, and I worked back and forth between those houses.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I came back to the United States.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they hadn't allowed me to take parachuting for fear I'd break my legs and couldn't train on other-- in other subjects.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I came back, and I was under Arthur Goldberg, who later became a Justice of the Supreme Court.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
